dismissalText.commentary: Michael Clarke c †Sangakkara b Eranga 47 (67b 3x4 0x6 94m) SR: 70.14

dismissalComment.html: Eranga has struck, this is a big blow, Clarke is gone, and Australia have two new batsmen at the crease, that was a short of length ball, pitching just outside off, goes on with angle and induces the outside edge, Clarke's patient innings comes to an end

Malinga you beauty, that spot-on yorker is far too good for Johnson, who was striving to get his bat down and keep that out but the ball zips past the batsman's defence and crashes into the bottom of legstump

headshotImage.caption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Malinga is on a hat-trick now, or is Australia going to review this lbw?  They have reviewed it. It was a low full toss, swinging dangerously in, the new batsman John Hastings couldn't keep it out, thuds into his pads, struck in front of legstump, umpire upholds the appeal, was it going down? the replay shows it would have taken the outside of leg stump, have to stick with the umpire's call for that, which means Hastings is gone for a golden duck

hat-trick for Malinga, another of those laser-guided low full tosses, Xavier Doherty has no chance, the middle stump is rattled, and Australia are down to 211 for 9, so much for the Powerplay, that's Malinga's third hat-trick in one-dayers, the most anyone has ever taken

commentTextItems.html: it's all over, the final stretch was a hard grind but Sri Lanka have finally made it past the finish line, and it was a streaky shot that confirmed the win, an outside edge past the second slip for four, Sri Lanka are back to No. 2, India slip to No. 3 in both Tests and ODIs on the same day

commentPostTextItems.html: I'd normally be required to do a short summary of the series here, but Dan B has done my job. Read his thoughts on the one-day series here.
Mahela Jayawardene gets an award first for completing 350 ODIs.
The Man of the Match is Lasith Malinga. Three of the previous seven one-day tricks are by Malinga.

Tillakaratne Dilshan: " Definitely, we have performed well today. The bowlers put in a fantastic effort. Today the middle order did the job for us. Chamara Silva batted really nice and his partnership with Jayawardene set up the win. Last Test series we really did well in England, and are looking forward to doing well in a couple of weeks time."

Michael Clarke is the Man of the Series: "Stoked to win the series, disappointing how today went but there is still a long way to go in this series. John came back really well towards the end of his spell, Patto started really well. We want to win every game we play, we have got some work to do in preparation for the Tests, the test guys have been here for a week and working hard."
A beaming Clarke collects the series trophy, and the Australian team gathers round it for photos. So Australia take the series 3-2, the Tests start on August 31st. See you then.

dismissalText.commentary: Mitchell Johnson b Malinga 1 (4b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: Malinga you beauty, that spot-on yorker is far too good for Johnson, who was striving to get his bat down and keep that out but the ball zips past the batsman's defence and crashes into the bottom of legstump

headshotImage.longCaption: John Hastings player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: John Hastings lbw b Malinga 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Malinga is on a hat-trick now, or is Australia going to review this lbw?  They have reviewed it. It was a low full toss, swinging dangerously in, the new batsman John Hastings couldn't keep it out, thuds into his pads, struck in front of legstump, umpire upholds the appeal, was it going down? the replay shows it would have taken the outside of leg stump, have to stick with the umpire's call for that, which means Hastings is gone for a golden duck

dismissalText.commentary: Xavier Doherty b Malinga 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: hat-trick for Malinga, another of those laser-guided low full tosses, Xavier Doherty has no chance, the middle stump is rattled, and Australia are down to 211 for 9, so much for the Powerplay, that's Malinga's third hat-trick in one-dayers, the most anyone has ever taken

dismissalComment.html: and the Australian inninigs has come to a rather rapid end, Mendis gets his third as Haddin tamely chips the ball to mid-off, Australua bowled out for 211, with nearly four overs remaining, two overs ago Australia were 210 for 5

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga c †Haddin b Johnson 0 (4b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Tharanga is gone, Johnson strikes in the first over, short of length ball outside off, Tharanga fishes at it, a thin edge through to the keeper

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan b Pattinson 17 (16b 3x4 0x6 28m) SR: 106.25

dismissalComment.html: got him! Pattinson continues to catch the eye in this opening burst, after peppering Dilshan with the short stuff, he slips in a quick full ball, Dilshan is caught on the crease, he inside-edges that onto the pad, and the ball homes in on offstump, superb bowling from Pattinson

dismissalText.commentary: Kumar Sangakkara c †Haddin b Pattinson 7 (7b 1x4 0x6 6m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: A big wicket for Australia, Sangakkara joins Tharanga in the pavilion, he is also drawn towards a short of length ball outside off, top edged to the keeper, Sri Lanka slip to 12 for 2
